The cache_v2 committed baseline is keyed by the HEAD span-tree OID and resolved committed_only, so it enumerates spans via committed_span_names (HEAD tree only, excluding index and worktree); enumerating worktree or index spans instead would bake untracked or uncommitted span files into a HEAD-keyed entry, making the warm-clean cache replay deleted or phantom spans — a correctness contract the types do not enforce.
